result.execSummary:
The defendant Matthew D Molitor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Arm Self w/ Dangerous Weapon, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(2)(b).
  • Burglary-Arm Self w/ Dangerous Weapon, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Matthew D Molitor in court, in custody, with attorney Katie B. Bricco.   Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Both parties are requesting to proceeding with plea and sentence, and to proceed without a PSI. Defendant enters a no contest plea to counts #2 & #3. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of counts #2 & #3. Count #1 is dismissed and read in. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Bricco makes statements regarding sentencing. Defendant makes Statements. Defendant is sentenced to the following.

IMPOSED SENTENCE OF:   

5.5 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 101 days)		***CONCURRENT TO COUNT #3***
  -  2.5 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT

____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;

COSTS:  $278.00 + $250.00 DNA surcharge. (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision)
